## Source
Architecture review 2026-07-15 candidate 8 (Speculative). Report: ~/served-html/architecture-review-hark-latest.html

## Problem
- `providers/auth.py` is deep (multi-store discovery)
- `providers/resolve.py` is a shallow if/elif factory
- Adapters re-resolve tokens per TTS chunk; Google bypasses shared auth
- Doctor + `hark providers` re-build status rows in parallel

## Investigate
1. `get_token(provider)` inject into STT/TTS adapters (resolve once)
2. Provider registry (pattern already cleaner in `agents/resolve`)
3. Fold Google into same auth seam
4. `all_provider_status()` as pure projection of that seam

## Outcome if promoted
Milestone under architecture revamp when voice deepens land. Real multi-adapter seam already exists for STT/TTS (ADR-004 cloud-first).

